cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for deep reinforcement learning using a recurrent neural network, which is a popular approach in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of prior knowledge and learning from data, which are common themes in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method is evaluated on a vision-based navigation task, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and the slow learning process involves training the weights of the RNN, which is a form of neural network (cs.NE).
